The paper focuses on learning visual recognition models from large scale web data, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of meta information (e.g., title, description, tags) in the web images, which relates to information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep CNN models, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
